To address the user's request, we need to add a delete button to cards in the UI and connect it to a new backend delete route. 

First, let's consider the UI aspect. The implementation details may vary depending on the frontend technology stack being used. However, the general idea is to add a delete button to each card and handle its click event to send a request to the backend delete route.

Here's a high-level example of how the UI part could be implemented:

```html
&lt;!-- Card component with delete button --&gt;
&lt;div class="card"&gt;
  &lt;!-- Card content --&gt;
  &lt;button class="delete-button"&gt;Delete&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
```

And the accompanying JavaScript code:

